In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. discusses the significance of Flag Day and National Flag Week in the United States. He emphasizes that the American flag represents the enduring strength and promise of the nation, symbolizing the story of an ever-evolving nation that values freedom, equality, and justice. The flag is seen as a beacon of democracy and a reminder of the sacrifices made by generations of Americans to ensure the endurance of democracy. President Biden encourages all Americans to display the flag during this week and honor the service members who have defended their freedoms. He also calls for the observance of Flag Day through Independence Day as a time to celebrate American history and values, and to recite the Pledge of Allegiance. The article concludes with President Biden's proclamation officially designating June 14 as Flag Day and the week starting June 11 as National Flag Week.